main event: A MAPS C-124 aircraft crew sighted a yellow or amber colored object shaped like a Jack-O-lantern at 25,000 feet near Okinawa, Ryuku Island on February 11, 1955.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be traveling at a speed of 1000 MPH.
No maneuver was observed by the crew.
The report considered the sighting as 'unknown' due to the reliability of the crew and good weather conditions, but the data was considered insufficient for a definitive evaluation.
The case was carried as 'insufficient data' in the Project Blue Book records.
No further report was found in the FILI (presumably the USAF file) regarding this sighting.
sighted object: yellow or amber colored object shaped like a Jack-O-lantern
